      "date": "2011-09-13 22:22:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIf o2iblnd needs to support aliased interfaces, then this patch alone is not enough. Aliased interfaces can fail in kiblnd_startup():                                                                       \n\n2874         if (strlen(ifname) >= sizeof(ibdev->ibd_ifname)) {                          \n2875                 CERROR(\"IPoIB interface name too long: %s\\n\", ifname);              \n2876                 goto failed;                                                        \n2877         }\n\nLinux allows alias names up to IFALIASZ, which is larger than sizeof(ibdev->ibd_ifname).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
